1) get N9 kernel source from:

http://harmattan-dev.nokia.com/pool/harmattan-beta3/free/k/kernel/kernel_2.6.32-20113701.10+0m6.tar.gz

2) get the wireless-compat from:

http://linuxwireless.org/download/compat-wireless-2.6/compat-wireless-2011-12-18.tar.bz2

3) get the bluez tree with latest development LE support:

git clone -b integration-v3 git://git.infradead.org/users/vcgomes/bluez.git

4) build bluez, kernel and modules:

./build_for_n9.sh

All done! Files built:

- kernel: kernel-2.6.32/build/arch/arm/boot/zImage
- kernel modules: kernel-modules.tar
- bluez: bluez-bin.tar

